"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748216","Home Office","false","2017-07-11","<p>The Home Office and the National Police Chiefs’ Council jointly hosted a meeting on 4 July with medical experts, police, retailers, and officials from a number of Government departments and agencies to share understanding about the nature of attacks and discussed action being taken by the respective agencies. We are currently considering with retailers what action can be taken to restrict access to the most harmful products used in acid and other corrosive substance attacks.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2017-07-11T12:40:33.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748216/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748216/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748216/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-07-04","Corrosive Substances: Sales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, with reference to the Answers to the hon. Member for East Ham of 23 March 2017 to Questions 68535 and 68460, whether the Government plans to bring forward legislation to (a) control the sale and purchase of products with high acidic content and (b) restrict by age of consumer the sale and purchase of such products.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","2974"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748217","Home Office","false","2017-07-12","<p>The Government is determined to cut off the funding which fuels the evils of extremism in the UK. In November 2015, the Government commissioned a review into the funding of Islamist extremist activity in the UK, including any overseas sources. The review reported to the Home Secretary and Prime Minister in 2016 and it has improved the Government’s understanding of the nature, scale and sources of funding for Islamist extremism in the UK.</p><p>The Government has updated Parliament on the review’s main findings on Wednesday 12 July 2017.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-07-12T12:27:36.603Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748217/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748217/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748217/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-07-04","Terrorism: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether she plans to publish a report on the funding of extremist activities in the UK by foreign governments, entities or individuals.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","2977"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748218","Home Office","false","2017-07-10","<p>No statistical information is available showing whether British citizens hold another citizenship. There is also no statistical information available to show the time taken to process applications for a change of name due to marriage.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-07-10T10:25:23.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748218/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748218/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748218/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-07-04","Passports: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what recent estimate she has made of the average time taken to process changes to passports for women holding dual nationality after those women have notified a name change after their marriage; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Laurence Robertson","Tewkesbury","Mr Laurence Robertson","2980"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748219","Cabinet Office","false","2017-07-11","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-07-11T14:06:45.387Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748219/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748219/answer","PQ2776 final.pdf","UKSA Response to PQ2776","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748219/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-07-04","EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many non-UK EU citizens, by country of origin are currently living in the UK.","true","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","2776"
