"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748261","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-07-12","<p>Over the course of 2017, to date, one Resident Judge has been appointed to the First-tier Tribunal, Immigration and Asylum Chamber.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2017-07-12T15:51:51.36Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748261/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748261/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748261/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-07-04","Immigration: Judges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many new immigration judges were appointed in 2017.","true","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","2782"
