"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748308","Women and Equalities","false","2017-07-14","<p>The Government is exploring a number of options to extend protections from discrimination in the workplace, including through the Equality Act 2010, for people with mental health conditions. We will make an announcement on these issues in due course.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2017-07-14T13:57:45.6Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748308/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748308/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748308/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2017-07-04","Mental Illness: Discrimination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, what plans she has to extend provisions in the Equalities Act 2010 related to protection against discrimination to mental health conditions that are episodic and fluctuating; and whether such provisions will include people with epilepsy.","false","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","Chipping Barnet","Theresa Villiers","2947"
