"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748329","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-10","<p>The available information on overturned Employment and Support Allowance (ESA) appeals can be found in the ESA Outcomes of Work Capability Assessments quarterly statistics published here - see Table 3 (Latest Release) :</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/employment-and-support-allowance-outcomes-of-work-capability-assessment" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/employment-and-support-allowance-outcomes-of-work-capability-assessment</a></p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-07-10T13:20:01.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748329/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748329/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748329/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-04","Employment and Support Allowance: Appeals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what proportion of applications for employment and support allowance which are rejected are overturned at the appeals stage.","false","Biography information for Rachel Reeves","Leeds West","Rachel Reeves","2883"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748330","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-10","<p>For the purposes of this response, we have interpreted ‘<em>protected disclosures’ as a </em>referral received via the DWP Whistle-blowers Hotline that has been classified under the definitions in the Public Interest Disclosure Act 1998 (PIDA). We have interpreted <em>‘staff alleged detriment’ </em>as staff members reporting a grievance.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong> </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015/16</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2016/17</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2017/18*</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Protected disclosures received (Whistle-blower referrals)</p></td><td><p>41</p></td><td><p>27</p></td><td><p>9</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Protected disclosures found to be valid</p></td><td><p>11</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>1 (8 cases ongoing)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Staff alleging detriment as a result of these disclosures</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Staff leaving the Department as a result of detriment following raising a disclosure</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>*2017/18 data covers the period 1 April 2017 to 30 June 2017.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-07-10T14:18:54.83Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748330/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748330/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748330/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-04","Department for Work and Pensions: Disclosure of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many protected disclosures were made by staff in his Department in each of the last three years for which figures are available; how many of those disclosures were found to be valid; how many staff alleged detriment as a result of those disclosures; and how many staff subsequently left his Department's employment.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","2863"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748331","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-17","<p>The Coal Forum was set up following the 2006 Energy Review in order to bring together Government and the coal industry to work to “secure the long-term future of coal-fired power generation and UK coal production”. The Forum most recently met on 10th February 2016, 3rd February 2015 and 27th January 2014. Members of the Coal Forum have met officials within the Department more regularly.</p><p>I have this week written to the Independent Chair of the Forum to set out my view that it has now served its purpose and should formally be wound down. Officials and I will of course continue to engage with representatives from the industry as and when appropriate.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-07-17T08:48:32.19Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748331/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748331/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748331/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-07-04","UK Coal Forum: Meetings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what the dates were on which the Coal Forum met in each of the last three years; and when he plans to call a further meeting of that forum.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","2862"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748332","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-11","<p>The public sector pay cap does not apply to employees of Direct Rail Services Ltd.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-07-11T16:14:14.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748332/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748332/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748332/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-07-04","Direct Rail Services: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether the one per cent public sector pay cap applies to employees of Direct Rail Services Ltd.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","2858"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748333","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-11","<p>It would be inappropriate to speculate on a report that we’ve not seen or on the outcome. However, we remain in close contact with the steel and aluminium industry regarding this investigation.</p><p>We have made it very clear to the US that we are deeply concerned by any measures that would affect UK industry. My right hon. Friend the Secretary of State for International Trade visited Washington on 19-20 June, accompanied by senior officials from the BEIS steel team, for meetings with the Commerce Secretary and United States Trade Representative, to discuss a range of key UK interests including steel.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2017-07-11T10:46:15.24Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748333/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748333/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748333/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-07-04","Iron and Steel: USA","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether his Department has made an assessment of the potential effect on the UK steel industry of the US Administration imposing a 20 per cent tariff on steel imports to the US.","false","Biography information for Gill Furniss","Sheffield, Brightside and Hillsborough","Gill Furniss","2851"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748334","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-11","<p>Information on the eligible businesses that have been referred to designated finance platforms under the Bank Referral Scheme since its implementation will be published in due course.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2017-07-11T14:56:20.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748334/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748334/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748334/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-04","Business: Bank Services","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many and what proportion of eligible businesses have been referred to designated finance platforms under the Bank Referral Scheme since its implementation.","false","Biography information for Rachel Reeves","Leeds West","Rachel Reeves","2784"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748335","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-12","<p>The Department for Business Energy and Industrial Strategy (BEIS) has a whistleblowing policy and procedure in place which allows for civil servants to report a perceived wrongdoing within the department, including something that they believe goes against the core values in the Civil Service Code. The Public Interest Disclosure Act 1998 (PIDA) will apply in some of these cases, and provides protection to those that ‘blow the whistle’ in certain circumstances.</p><p>The figures provided in the table below show the total number of whistleblowing cases that were protected disclosures under PIDA (A).</p><p>The table goes on to show the number of cases found to be valid under PIDA (B), the number of employees that alleged detriment as a result of the disclosure under PIDA (C), and finally the number of employees who made a disclosure under PIDA, alleged detriment as a result of a disclosure and subsequently left the department (D).</p><p>As BEIS was formed on 14<sup>th</sup> July 2016 we are only able to provide data from that date.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p><strong>A. Number of whistleblowing cases that were covered under PIDA</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>B. Number of cases found to be valid under PIDA</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>C. Number of employees that alleged detriment as a result of the disclosure under PIDA</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>D. Number of employees who subsequently left the department (i.e. after making a disclosure and then alleged detriment as a result of the disclosure)</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2016/17</strong></p></td><td><p>Less than 5</p></td><td><p>Less than 5</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong> </strong></p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-07-12T15:57:03.05Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748335/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748335/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748335/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-07-04","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Disclosure of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many protected disclosures were made by staff in his Department in each of the last three years for which figures are available; how many of those disclosures were found to be valid; how many staff alleged detriment as a result of having made a protected disclosure; and how many of those staff subsequently left the employment of the Department.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","2878"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748336","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-12","<p>The Government routinely publishes total import figures from interconnectors in the annual Digest of UK Energy Statistics (DUKES), and the quarterly National Statistics Energy Trends data.</p><p> </p><p>The latest available 12 month period of data spans 1 April 2016 to 31 March 2017 and shows a gross import of 17,228 GWh through interconnectors.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-07-12T10:47:46.133Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748336/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748336/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748336/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-07-04","Electricity: Consumption","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many GWh of electricity consumed in the UK in the last 12 months were supplied by interconnectors.","false","Biography information for Sir William Cash","Stone","Sir William Cash","2893"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748337","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-12","<p>In the 12 months ending March 2017, the total UK electricity demand, which includes energy industry use, losses and final consumption by end users, was 354.5 TWh. This is down 0.7 per cent on the same period a year earlier.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Source: Energy Trends table 5.2 - <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/electricity-section-5-energy-trends" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/electricity-section-5-energy-trends</a></p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-07-12T10:45:34.787Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748337/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748337/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748337/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-07-04","Electricity: Consumption","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many TWh of electricity were consumed in the UK in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Sir William Cash","Stone","Sir William Cash","2892"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748338","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-12","<p>The UK currently has 4GW (4000MW) of operational interconnection capacity:</p><p> </p><ul><li>IFA (Interconnexion France-Angleterre); 2GW (2000MW) from Folkestone, Kent to Calais, France, operating since 1986;</li><li>Moyle; 500MW between South Ayrshire, Scotland and County Antrim, Northern Ireland, operating since 2002;</li><li>Britned; 1GW (1000MW) from the Isle of Grain, Kent, to Rotterdam in the Netherlands, operating since 2011;</li><li>East-West (EWIC); 500MW connecting Barkby Beach, North Wales to Dublin, Ireland, operating since 2012.</li></ul><p> </p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-07-12T10:42:46.217Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748338/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748338/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748338/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-07-04","Electricity Interconnectors","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what operational interconnectors there are in the UK; and what the MW capacity is of each of those interconnectors.","false","Biography information for Sir William Cash","Stone","Sir William Cash","2896"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748339","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-12","<p>The Government routinely publishes total export figures in the annual Digest of UK Energy Statistics (DUKES), and the quarterly National Statistics Energy Trends data.</p><p> </p><p>The latest available 12 month period of data spans March 2016 to March 2017 and shows a total export of 2,782 GWh through interconnectors.</p><p> </p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-07-12T10:40:42.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748339/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748339/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748339/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-07-04","Electricity: Exports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many GWh of electricity were exported from the UK through interconnectors in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Sir William Cash","Stone","Sir William Cash","2894"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748340","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-12","<p>The Government routinely publishes total import figures from interconnectors in the annual Digest of UK Energy Statistics (DUKES), and the quarterly National Statistics Energy Trends data.</p><p> </p><p>Electricity imported to the UK from January 2012 to end March 2017 amounts to the following:</p><p> </p><ul><li>IFA (Interconnexion France-Angleterre) (France-England): 59.7 TWh;</li><li>BritNed (Netherlands-England): 37.7 TWh;</li><li>EWIC (East-West Interconnector) (Ireland-Wales): 2.3 TWh;</li><li>NSI (North-South Interconnector) (Ireland-Northern Ireland): 1.1 TWh.</li></ul><p> </p><p>In addition, 1.26 TWh were imported into GB from Northern Ireland.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-07-12T10:36:00.863Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748340/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748340/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748340/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-07-04","Electricity: Imports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many TWh of electricity have been imported into the UK by individual interconnectors since 2012.","false","Biography information for Sir William Cash","Stone","Sir William Cash","2895"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748341","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-12","<p>On 15th June National Grid released the capacity market timetable for 2017/18 and within it they have indicated that the T-4 auction will start on 6th February. Please find a link to the timetable document here: <a href="https://www.emrdeliverybody.com/Lists/Latest%20News/Attachments/109/Capacity%20Market%20Operational%20Plan%202017.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.emrdeliverybody.com/Lists/Latest%20News/Attachments/109/Capacity%20Market%20Operational%20Plan%202017.pdf</a></p><p> </p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-07-12T10:33:37.3Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748341/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748341/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748341/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-07-04","Electricity Generation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether the T-4 capacity market auction for delivery in October 2021 will take place in February 2018; and and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir William Cash","Stone","Sir William Cash","2901"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748342","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-12","<p>National Grid Electricity Transmission plc (NGET), in its role as system operator, have informed us that the average transmission network use of system charge for a GB generator is £5.77 / kW (2017/18 tariffs). The actual tariff is dependent on the location of the generator, the historic load factor of the generator, the type of generator and details of its specific connection.</p><p> </p><p>As part of the overall transmission infrastructure facilitating the wider market, interconnectors do not pay use of system charges for the transmission network. As producers and consumers are liable for charges in their own countries, additional charges for using the interconnector, to allow imports and exports, would amount to double charging and may hinder the ability of GB producers to export electricity to other countries.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-07-12T10:30:57.857Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748342/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748342/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748342/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-07-04","Electricity: Costs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what the average cost is of transmission network costs for (a) interconnectors and (b) domestic generators of electricity.","false","Biography information for Sir William Cash","Stone","Sir William Cash","2900"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748343","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-12","<p>The UK has a pipeline of interconnector projects that are expected to play a role in providing reliable, affordable, and clean energy.</p><p> </p><p>Based on current project timelines and assuming all projects are able to complete, 3GW (3000MW) of new interconnector capacity are expected to be operational by 2020. A further 1.4GW is also currently under construction for delivery after 2020. There are a further 9.5GW of projects which have sought regulatory approval.</p><p> </p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-07-12T10:27:54.83Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748343/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748343/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748343/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-07-04","Electricity Interconnectors","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many megawatts of new interconnector capacity are proposed by (a) 2020 and (b) 2025.","false","Biography information for Sir William Cash","Stone","Sir William Cash","2897"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748344","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-11","<p>The proportion of electricity that will be supplied by electricity imports by 2020 is expected to be 7.6%.</p><p> </p><p>The power supply sector is projected using the reference case scenario from the Energy and Emissions Projections 2016 (published March 2017), which can be found here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/updated-energy-and-emissions-projections-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/updated-energy-and-emissions-projections-2016</a></p><p> </p><p>Up to 2020, the reference scenario reflects current power sector policies. Beyond 2020, the reference scenario includes assumptions that go beyond current Government policy. The results do not indicate a preferred outcome and should be treated as illustrative.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-07-11T14:44:28.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748344/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748344/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748344/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-07-04","Electricity Interconnectors","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what proportion of electricity will be supplied by interconnectors in (a) 2020 and (b) 2025.","false","Biography information for Sir William Cash","Stone","Sir William Cash","2898"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748345","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-11","<p>The Government does not hold prices on electricity imports over interconnectors. This is commercial information held by market participants.</p><p> </p><p>As regards the average price for other electricity generation, the average UK power price in the day ahead market, the most commonly cited trading time frame, was £45.01 over the past 12 months. This is an incomplete picture as power is sold across a number of time frames, from year ahead through to intraday trading, and it would be inappropriate to extract wholesale prices from one time frame and use it to infer prices across other time frames. The Government does not have visibility of longer term time frames, which is commercial information held by market participants.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-07-11T14:42:42.69Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748345/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748345/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748345/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-07-04","Electricity: Prices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what the average price of electricity supplied by (a) interconnectors and (b) other electricity generation was in the last year for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Sir William Cash","Stone","Sir William Cash","2899"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748346","Department for Education","false","2017-07-10","<p>Tackling social mobility is at the heart of the government’s ambition to make Britain a country that works for everyone. As part of this, we are committed to ensuring that high quality apprenticeships are accessible to people of all ages and from all backgrounds.</p><p> </p><p>Apprenticeships are paid jobs with training and can be used to train and upskill existing employees as well as a means of recruiting new staff.</p><p> </p><p>It is important that people of all ages and backgrounds are able to achieve the long term benefits associated with completing an apprenticeship in terms of increased wages and career progression.</p><p> </p><p>We are providing additional funding to support young people and those from disadvantaged areas to access apprenticeships, recognising where the costs of supporting an apprentice are higher. This includes additional payments for both employers and training providers when they take on 16 to 18 year olds or 19 to 24 year olds who were in care or who have an Education, Health and Care Plan, and cash payments to providers for training individuals from the top 27% of deprived areas.</p><p> </p><p>Our ‘Get In Go Far’ campaign aims to inspire more young people to take on an apprenticeship, and more employers to offer them.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2017-07-10T16:38:04.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748346/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748346/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748346/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-07-04","Apprentices: Age","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, with reference to page 4 of the Social Mobility Commission report Time for Change, published on 28 June 2017, for what reasons more older than younger workers have obtained apprenticeships.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","2750"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748347","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-10","<p>The information requested is not held by the Department at this time.</p><p>The Department maintains the Renewable Energy Planning Database (REPD), which tracks the progress of new renewable energy projects, including onshore wind projects, as they move through the planning system. The database is updated and published on a monthly basis. An update for June 2017 will be published shortly on the Department’s website at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/renewable-energy-planning-database-monthly-extract" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/renewable-energy-planning-database-monthly-extract</a></p><p>It should be noted that the REPD shows projects that have applied for planning permission in the previous month or earlier for projects with a capacity greater than, or equal to, 1MW. Therefore, planning applications that were submitted in June may appear in later monthly REPD updates.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-07-10T16:28:27.59Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748347/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748347/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748347/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-07-04","Wind Power: Planning Permission","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether any planning applications have been submitted for new onshore wind farms since 9 June 2017; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","2753"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748348","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-10","<p>The Government has been recently elected and its approach to implementing the manifesto proposals, including the establishment of a Shale Environmental Regulator, has yet to be finalised.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-07-10T16:28:51.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748348/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748348/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748348/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-07-04","Fracking: Regulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what his policy is on establishing a Shale Environmental Regulator; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","2752"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748349","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-11","<p>Progress has been made in recent years to improve competition in the domestic retail gas with households now having a choice of around 55 companies supplying gas. Smaller suppliers are continuing to grow their market share and now have just over 18% of the domestic retail gas market.</p><p>We have reduced by half the time it takes to switch suppliers and are working with Ofgem to move to even faster and more reliable switching. Ofgem are working on developing better ways to engage consumers and on 3 July announced trials to help customers on expensive standard tariffs find and switch to cheaper energy deals.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-07-11T08:45:20.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748349/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748349/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748349/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-07-04","Natural Gas: Competition","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what steps he is taking to further improve competition in the domestic gas industry; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Greg Knight","East Yorkshire","Sir Greg Knight","2760"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748350","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-10","<p>The Department of Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy prepares biennial reports to the United Nations on the UK’s progress in tackling climate change, which include an assessment of the technical and financial support that HMG provides to other countries to assist them to deploy clean energy. The most recent report can be found on the United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change (UNFCCC) website: <a href="http://unfccc.int/files/national_reports/biennial_reports_and_iar/submitted_biennial_reports/application/pdf/20151218_uk_biennial_report_2_web_accessible.pdf" target="_blank">http://unfccc.int/files/national_reports/biennial_reports_and_iar/submitted_biennial_reports/application/pdf/20151218_uk_biennial_report_2_web_accessible.pdf</a>. Chapter 5 sets out an overview of the financial and technical support provided and Table 7 in Annex 1 provides details of individual projects.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-07-10T16:31:32.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748350/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748350/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748350/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-07-04","Renewable Energy: Technology Transfer","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment he has made of the role the Government is playing in facilitating technological transfer to smaller countries to grow their renewable energy sectors and reduce dependence on fossil fuels.","false","Biography information for Dawn Butler","Brent Central","Dawn Butler","2761"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748351","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-12","<p>We remain firmly committed to bringing forward the UK’s first new nuclear power plants in a generation.</p><p>The Hinkley Point C contracts make provision for compensation in certain defined circumstances. The details of when these apply are set out in the agreements.</p><p>The consequences of the intended withdrawal from the Euratom Treaty will be closely monitored and the department is in close consultation with the industry about its impacts.</p><p>The Government will continue to support Euratom and to ensure that the UK continues to meet its international safeguards, and nuclear non-proliferation obligations and support its thriving nuclear industry.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-07-12T15:26:37.66Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748351/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748351/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748351/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-07-04","Hinkley Point C Power Station: Compensation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment he has made of the risk that the UK's withdrawal from the European Atomic Energy Community would trigger compensation clauses in the investor agreement in relation to Hinkley Point C power station.","false","Biography information for Dr Alan Whitehead","Southampton, Test","Dr Alan Whitehead","2729"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748352","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-10","<p>The UK has provided 9% of donor funding to the 6th replenishment of the Global Environment Facility (GEF6). Total funding for GEF6 including projected investment income and other sources of finance is expected to be $4.43bn (2014-2018). The GEF is currently providing $2.3m to the Low Greenhouse Gas Emissions (LGGE) Project, a programme which is promoting Energy Efficiency and Renewable Energy in Buildings in Jamaica.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-07-10T16:30:23.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748352/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748352/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748352/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-07-04","Renewable Energy: Jamaica","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what steps the Government is taking to support the transfer of technology to Jamaica in relation to the renewable energy programme in that country.","false","Biography information for Dawn Butler","Brent Central","Dawn Butler","2769"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748353","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-10","<p>BEIS run a quarterly survey of domestic electricity and gas suppliers. This survey has coverage of around 85 per cent of the market. Data is supplied to BEIS, on numbers of customers by tariff by region by payment type, but as this data is supplied in confidence, individual tariff or company data cannot be made publically available.</p><p>Aggregate statistics are produced and published as part of our quarterly energy prices (QEP) publication. In quarter 1 2017, we estimate 66 per cent of standard electricity and 65 per cent of gas customers were on variable tariffs. Our current methodology does not breakout standard variable tariffs from other variable tariffs.</p><p>Data can be found here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/quarterly-domestic-energy-price-stastics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/quarterly-domestic-energy-price-stastics</a></p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-07-10T16:31:49.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748353/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748353/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748353/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-07-04","Energy: Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what information his Department holds on how many households are on energy suppliers' standard variable rates.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","2705"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748354","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-11","<p>There are no security of supply implications arising from the potential change in ownership of NuGen. The UK has established processes through the Capacity Market to ensure security of supply through a diverse range of generation assets.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-07-11T10:48:30.68Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748354/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748354/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748354/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-07-04","Nuclear Power Stations: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment he has made of the effect on UK energy security of any change in ownership of the NuGen power station at Moorside; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","2718"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748355","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-11","<p>Toshiba are considering options for the sale of NuGen, who are currently undertaking an internal strategic review looking at options to take forward their proposed project at Moorside. The project timetable will be dependent on decisions made in the light of this review.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-07-11T10:47:20.1Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748355/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748355/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748355/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-07-04","Nuclear Power Stations: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what estimate he has made of the completion date for the NuGen nuclear power station at Moorside; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","2719"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748356","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-11","<p>We are increasing public investment in research and development investment by £4.7 billion over the period 2017-18 to 2020-21. This equates to an extra £2 billion per year by 2020-21 and is an increase of around 20% to total government R&amp;D spending, more than any increase in any parliament since 1979.</p><p>We are creating the right environment to incentivise private sector investment in R&amp;D. Innovate UK currently provides funding for research, development and demonstration projects and has funded over 11,000 projects to date, with over 8,000 unique organisations involved.Through Innovate UK, we have established a network of Catapult Centres to commercialise new and emerging technologies and Catapults are forecast to attract total public and private investment exceeding £1.6bn over their first five years of operation. R&amp;D tax credits encourage greater R&amp;D investment by business and in the year ending 31 March 2015 almost 21,000 companies used the R&amp;D tax credits to claim a total amount of £2.45 billion, with R&amp;D expenditure used to make these claims reaching £21.8 billion.</p><p>Science, Research and Innovation will be at the heart of our Industrial Strategy and this Government has bold ambitions to increase R&amp;D and back industries of the future. Our commitment to reach R&amp;D investment of 2.4% of GDP within ten years and 3% in the longer-term is part of this.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2017-07-11T16:12:03.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748356/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748356/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748356/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-07-04","Research: Private Sector","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what incentives his Department provides to the private sector to increase expenditure on research and development.","false","Biography information for Liam Byrne","Birmingham, Hodge Hill","Liam Byrne","2975"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748357","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-24","<p>The UK imports a wide variety of radioactive isotopes for medical use. These include radioisotopes used for medical imaging of cancers and for cancer therapy. As medical radio-isotopes are not special fissile material, they are not subject to international safeguards and their availability in the UK should not be impacted by withdrawal from Euratom.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-07-24T12:54:02.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748357/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748357/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748357/answer","Watford","Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748357/answer/previousversion/3149","Biography information for Richard Harrington","201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-07-04","EURATOM","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment he has made of the effect of the UK withdrawing from Euratom on cancer research in the UK.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","2969"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748358","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-13","<p>The Department is working closely across Government and with industry to assess this. Around 20% of the UK’s electricity comes from nuclear power. In order to ensure the continued success of the civil nuclear industry and nuclear energy production, a Bill to establish a domestic nuclear safeguards regime was included in the Queen’s Speech. This is being taken forward as a matter of urgency alongside other measures also being implemented, including international negotiations. The UK secured agreement with the EU that a Euratom Working Group should commence negotiations this month as a priority. The Government is determined that the UK continues to meet its international safeguards, and nuclear non-proliferation obligations and support its thriving nuclear industry.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-07-13T14:59:24.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748358/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748358/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748358/answer","Watford","Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748358/answer/previousversion/3152","Biography information for Richard Harrington","201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-07-04","EURATOM","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment he has made of the effect of the UK withdrawing from Euratom on energy production in the UK.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","2970"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748359","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-07-10","<p>DExEU Ministers continue to work closely with their colleagues across Government to ensure that we are speaking with a broad range of people, who reflect the diversity of the UK. The Department is also engaging, at both Ministerial and official level, with groups and organisations who support and represent the diverse communities of the UK. We will continue to hear from these groups throughout the negotiation process.</p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2017-07-10T16:34:26.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748359/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748359/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748359/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-07-04","Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, if he will take steps to ensure that the interests of people from diverse communities are represented during the negotiations on the UK exiting the EU.","false","Biography information for Dawn Butler","Brent Central","Dawn Butler","2771"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748360","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-07-10","<p>The Department for Exiting the European Union receives legal services from the Government Legal Department so has not directly employed any civil servants or secondees as specialist lawyers. Currently there are approximately 40 GLD lawyers working for the benefit of DExEU and the costs of this work will be published in the Annual Report and Accounts shortly.</p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2017-07-10T16:31:21.863Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748360/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748360/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748360/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-07-04","Department for Exiting the European Union: Legal Profession","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how many civil servants has been employed by his Department as specialist lawyers since its creation; what the pay grades are of those officials; how many lawyers have been seconded to his Department, from which firms, since its creation; and how much has been spent on such external legal advice and services.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","2904"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748361","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-07-12","<p>The Department for Exiting the European Union is committed to the creation of a diverse and inclusive working environment to ensure staff do not face any barriers to success, and all staff feel supported at work. As such, the Department is committed to the steps established in the Civil Service 2016 Talent Action Plan to help the Civil Service become the most inclusive employer in the UK. The Department is also committed to working with a diverse range of external organisations, to ensure our work reflects a broad range of opinions across the UK.</p><p>The Department has an active equalities network to provide support and has appointed Catherine Webb as the dedicated senior equalities champion who sits on the Department's Executive Board and provides support and board level representation for the equalities networks. The department has dedicated mental health first aiders and has signed the Time to Change pledge in February 2017. Additionally DExEU has subscribed to the Disability Confident Employer Scheme and the two tick guaranteed interview scheme. We also intend to participate in the Stonewall equality index benchmarking exercise and the Social Mobility Index.</p><p> </p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2017-07-12T16:39:16.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748361/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748361/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748361/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-07-04","Department for Exiting the European Union: Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what steps he is taking to encourage diversity in his Department.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","2822"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749755","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-10","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave earlier today to the hon. Member for Peterborough (Fiona Onasanya).</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-07-10T16:04:14.993Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749755/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749755/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749755/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-04","Armed Forces: Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what discussions he had with contractors on their delivery of service accommodation; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Liz Twist","Blaydon","Liz Twist","900314"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749756","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-10","<p>The Royal Navy is growing for the first time in a generation. The first of two new aircraft carriers, HMS QUEEN ELIZABETH, is at sea conducting trials. There will be new submarines; frigates – we have placed the contract for the first three Type 26s; aircraft; patrol vessels; support ships and tankers. We will increase Naval personnel numbers by 400 to 30,600 by 2025.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-07-10T15:57:55.66Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749756/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749756/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749756/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-04","Navy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans he has to expand the Royal Navy.","false","Biography information for Bob Blackman","Harrow East","Bob Blackman","900312"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749757","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-10","<p>On 2 July, I announced the signature of a contract with BAE Systems worth around £3.7 billion to start the manufacture of the first batch of three Type 26 Frigates with the first steel to be cut later this month. This is an excellent deal for the taxpayer and a momentous commitment for Scotland that will strengthen and secure our shipbuilding industry on the Clyde for the future.</p>","Sevenoaks","Sir Michael Fallon",,"2017-07-10T16:53:18.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749757/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749757/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749757/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-04","Type 26 Frigates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what progress he has made on agreeing a contract for the Type 26 frigate.","false","Biography information for Andrew Bowie","West Aberdeenshire and Kincardine","Andrew Bowie","900309"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749758","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-10","<p>The UK has not taken part in negotiation of this treaty, and does not intend to sign, ratify or become party to it. It will not be binding on the UK. The UK does not accept that this treaty can constitute a development of customary international law binding on the UK or other non-parties. The UK continues to pursue step by step nuclear disarmament consistent with the Nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty.</p>","Sevenoaks","Sir Michael Fallon",,"2017-07-10T16:54:50.52Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749758/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749758/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749758/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-04","Nuclear Disarmament","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of the potential effect on his Department's policies of the draft treaty to prohibit nuclear weapons published by the UN in May 2017.","false","Biography information for Tommy Sheppard","Edinburgh East","Tommy Sheppard","900315"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749759","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-10","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave earlier today to the hon. Member for Telford (Lucy Allan).</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-07-10T15:55:24.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749759/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749759/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749759/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-04","Armed Forces Covenant","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps he is taking to strengthen the Armed Forces Covenant.","false","Biography information for Mike Wood","Dudley South","Mike Wood","900317"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749760","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-10","<p>HMS QUEEN ELIZABETH sailed from Rosyth on 26 June to commence contractor sea trials off the north-east coast of Scotland. HMS QUEEN ELIZABETH is by far the most powerful warship ever built in Britain enabling us to tackle changing threats around the globe.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-07-10T15:57:24.25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749760/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749760/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749760/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-04","HMS Queen Elizabeth","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what progress he has made on bringing the Queen Elizabeth class aircraft carriers into service.","false","Biography information for Neil Parish","Tiverton and Honiton","Neil Parish","900316"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749761","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-10","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave earlier today to the hon. Member for Weaver Vale (Mike Amesbury).</p>","Sevenoaks","Sir Michael Fallon",,"2017-07-10T15:55:48.583Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749761/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749761/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749761/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-04","Armed Forces: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what recent discussions he has had with the Armed Forces Pay Review Body on levels of pay for the armed forces.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","900313"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747322","Department for Education","false","2017-07-14","<p>Universities are autonomous bodies and it is for them to determine pay arrangements for their staff. However, the Government, in the 2017/18 Higher Education Funding Council for England (HEFCE) grant letter stated:</p><p> </p><p>“The Government is clear that efficiency includes demonstrating restraint in senior pay and remains concerned about the substantial upwards drift in salaries of some top management. We would like to see senior leaders in the sector exercise more pay restraint.”</p><p> </p><p>Jo Johnson, the Minister for Universities and Science, has continued to call on the sector to show restraint in Vice Chancellors' pay and for the sector to demonstrate more leadership especially at a time when students are concerned about value for money.</p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Viscount Younger of Leckie",,"2017-07-14T10:38:01.997Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747322/answer","Biography information for Viscount Younger of Leckie","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747322/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747322/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-07-03",,"2","House of Lords","Her Majesty's Government what advice they, or their agencies, give to universities on the appropriate remuneration of vice-chancellors.","false","Biography information for Lord Adonis",,"Lord Adonis","HL309"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747324","Department for Education","false","2017-07-18","<p>Fees for English domiciled undergraduate students studying at Higher Education Institutions that are funded by the Higher Education Funding Council for England (HEFCE) are subject to maximum fees, which are set in legislation. HEFCE funded institutions that have an access agreement in place for widening participation with the Office for Fair Access (OFFA) can charge a higher fee than those that do not. In addition, HEFCE funded institutions that have demonstrated high quality teaching by achieving a Teaching Excellence Framework (TEF) rating can charge up to a higher fee than those that do not.</p><p> </p>",,"Viscount Younger of Leckie",,"2017-07-18T11:49:07.27Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747324/answer","Biography information for Viscount Younger of Leckie","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747324/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747324/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-07-03",,"2","House of Lords","Her Majesty's Government what advice they, or their agencies, give to universities on the appropriate fee level to set in respect of undergraduate courses.","false","Biography information for Lord Adonis",,"Lord Adonis","HL310"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747326","Department for Education","false","2017-07-14","<p>The government does not assess the fees of individual institutions. It sets maximum fees for eligible students in legislation. Only those institutions with an access agreement in place for widening participation with the Office for Fair Access (OFFA) can charge fees up to a highest cap.</p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Viscount Younger of Leckie",,"2017-07-14T10:38:21.997Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747326/answer","Biography information for Viscount Younger of Leckie","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747326/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747326/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-07-03",,"2","House of Lords","Her Majesty's Government whether, in the past 12 months, they, or their agencies, have advised any university, or universities, that proposed fee levels were unacceptably high; and if so, what that advice was.","false","Biography information for Lord Adonis",,"Lord Adonis","HL311"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747328","Department for International Trade","false","2017-07-17","<p>The Department for International Trade has a strong and capable trade policy team which has grown significantly since June 2016 (from 45 to over 300 today), and is continuing to grow.</p><p> </p><p>We continue to hire the brightest and best talent from within the UK civil service and externally, in order to build a world class trade policy team that can deliver the best outcomes for the UK.</p><p> </p><p>At this stage, the Department’s primary focus is on developing our trade policy positions, international relationships and approach to future trade negotiations to ensure we are in the best position to agree trade deals once we exit the EU.</p><p> </p><p>The Department has recently appointed Crawford Falconer to the role of Chief Trade Negotiation Adviser and Head of Trade Profession. Mr Falconer brings a wealth of global trade expertise from over 25 years of working on trade policy in the New Zealand government, the World Trade Organization and academia.</p>",,"Lord Price",,"2017-07-17T12:24:59.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747328/answer","Biography information for Lord Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747328/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747328/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-07-03",,"2","House of Lords","Her Majesty's Government how many officials with substantial experience of international trade negotiations have been appointed to the Department for International Trade.","false","Biography information for Lord Adonis",,"Lord Adonis","HL312"
