"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747505","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-07-11","<p>The creative industries, including the digital media industries, are the fastest growing part of the UK’s economy. The Government is committed to ensuring that the creative industries continue to thrive nationwide, including in York.</p><p> </p><p>This is why we are developing an ambitious Industrial Strategy that will drive growth across the country, bringing together local businesses as well as political and public sector leaders. We want to identify and support local specialisms and clusters of business. For many places, the creative industries will form a vital part of that thinking.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-07-11T12:38:57.923Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747505/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747505/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747505/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-07-03","Digital Technology: Urban Areas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what support her Department is providing to cities to grow their digital media industries.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","2371"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747506","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-07-06","<p>The Rural Payments Agency (RPA) does not hold information on Basic Payment Scheme (BPS) payments at a council level.</p><p> </p><p>As at close of business on 3 July, 99.7% of farmers in Cumbria have received their full BPS 2016 payment. There are 14 farmers still to receive their payment. Of these 7 are held subject to the completion of probate; 3 are complete but waiting on information from the Scottish Government; and 4 are still to complete processing.</p><p> </p><p>The RPA continues to focus on the completion of the remainder and dealing with any queries on BPS 2016 claims raised by farmers.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-07-06T16:20:43.39Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747506/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747506/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747506/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-07-03","Agriculture: Cumbria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many farmers in (a) South Lakeland District Council area and (b) Cumbria have not yet received their full basic payment scheme payment for 2016.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","2418"
